# Uploads Directory

This directory is reserved for user-uploaded files. Do not commit actual uploads to version control.

## Subdirectories

- **items/** - Product/item images uploaded by users
- **profiles/** - User profile pictures

## Important Notes

- This directory structure is tracked by Git, but actual uploaded files are ignored
- Ensure proper file permissions for web server write access
- Implement file size limits and validation on upload
- Use unique filenames to prevent conflicts (e.g., UUID + timestamp)

## Recommended File Naming Convention

```
{userId}_{timestamp}_{uuid}.{extension}
Example: 1234_20260409123045_a8f3c2e1.jpg
```

## Security Considerations

1. Validate file types (whitelist: jpg, jpeg, png, gif only)
2. Check file size limits (recommended: max 5MB per file)
3. Sanitize filenames to prevent directory traversal attacks
4. Store files outside document root if possible
5. Never execute uploaded files
6. Scan for malware in production environments

